JOHANNESBURG - The Mr Price Group's half-year profits are up by 24 percent. The company said its clothing and financial services divisions drove profits up.   But, the waning economy hammered the group's sports and home divisions. READ: Festive retail sales may help give GDP a boost Its revenue has grown to R9.8-billion. Operating profits are 22 percent higher, after climbing to R1.5-billion. Mr Price declared an interim dividend of 279 cents per share, up by 22.3 percent from the interim dividend a year earlier. eNCA